@NotNullDefault

Package com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.function

Fills in code missing from the java.util.function package, mostly with primitive-specialized functions. This package is separate in an attempt to keep a clean break between the rest of the library and code based on OpenJDK's GPL v2 (with classpath exception)-licensed code.
The interfaces in this package are all extremely simple and there's no way to implement them in a way that respects compatibility other than the way OpenJDK 8 does. OpenJDK's license is available here, if there's any confusion. If required, this entire package can be moved to an external dependency, which I believe would be unambiguously permitted by the classpath exception.
